Once they do that, they will then have to go back and check your character saves, to see what equipment you had.<br>
<br>
Now two things will cause this to have problems. 1) its too old and the logs are gone, or 2) You've gotten a bazzilion levels since then and restoring to last save would be rediculous.<br>
<br>
Like they said above, send one email to contact your gm, but dont sent a direct tell to a gm, they have to go in petition order, and because you &quot;cut in the line&quot; they cant do anything for you right away, and if they have to log, suddenly there's no one pleading your case 'cause ya didnt petition. Just petition every day and include ALL the details in your petition, where what when how and why and what you want. Dont get mad a the guides, even if they want to help you, they cant because they dont have access to the log files.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> In Perfect Hate, and Perfect Faith</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
